Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan on high heat. When hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and stir-fry ~{30%seconds}.

Add the lentils, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1.5%tsp} and @water{50%ml} (see pantry for both amounts). Stir to combine and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir through the @butter{20%g} (see pantry for amount) until melted. Remove from the heat. Taste the mixture and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #board (3 per person), spoon the mixture down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little oil over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll.

Sprinkle over the cheese, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, a drizzle of oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and a pinch of sugar.

Just before serving, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and toss to coat in the dressing.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the lentil and mushroom enchiladas between your plates. Serve the baby leaf salad alongside. Enjoy!